---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = 'Privacy';
const description =
	'What hungovercoders collects about you: cookieless, privacy-first traffic analytics and nothing more';
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main id="main-content" class="prose">
			<h1>Privacy</h1>

			<p>
				Short version: this site uses privacy-first, cookieless analytics to count visits and see
				which posts are read. There is <strong>no</strong> advertising, no cross-site tracking, and
				nothing stored on your device.
			</p>

			<h2>Cookies</h2>
			<p>
				hungovercoders sets no cookies and stores nothing on your device. Because of that there is no
				cookie banner because there is nothing to consent to.
			</p>

			<h2>Analytics</h2>
			<p>
				Traffic is measured with
				<a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare Web Analytics</a>,
				a privacy-first tool that uses no cookies and no client-side storage. It records aggregate
				metrics only: page views, the referring site, approximate country, and device or browser
				type. That helps me see how the site performs and which posts are useful.
			</p>
			<p>
				Your IP address is used momentarily at Cloudflare's edge to derive your approximate country
				and is <strong>not stored</strong>. There is no fingerprinting, no cross-site tracking, no
				advertising, and no selling of data. The legal basis for this limited processing is
				legitimate interest, and because nothing is stored on your device, no consent banner is
				required. See
				<a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare's privacy policy</a>
				for how they handle the data on my behalf.
			</p>
			<p>
				Cloudflare acts as my data processor for this, under its
				<a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/cloudflare-customer-dpa/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Data Processing Addendum</a>;
				any transfer of data outside the UK or EEA is covered by Standard Contractual Clauses and the
				UK/EU–US Data Privacy Framework. You have the right to ask what is held about you and to
				request its erasure. Since no identifying data is stored, there is nothing tied to you to
				retrieve. Questions go via the <a href="/about">About</a> page.
			</p>

			<h2>If this changes</h2>
			<p>
				If anything more than this is ever collected, this page will be updated first, describing
				exactly what is collected, why, the legal basis, and how to opt out. Any such tooling will be
				chosen to avoid collecting personal data wherever possible.
			</p>

			<p>Questions? Get in touch via the <a href="/about">About</a> page.</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.prose {
		max-width: calc(100% - 2em);
		margin: 3rem auto;
		padding: 0 1rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}
	.prose h1 {
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}
	.prose h2 {
		margin-top: 1.5em;
	}
</style>
